Governor Nasir El-Rufai of Kaduna State, has announced that one out of six patients with COVID-19 infection has been discharged. The Governor made this known via a tweet on his Twitter account on Wednesday. He said, ”Commissioner of Health, Dr. Amina Mohammed-Baloni has announced the recovery and discharge of one of the six Covid-19 patients in the state.” Recall that the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, on Tuesday, confirmed 19 new cases of Coronavirus across the country. An additional 11 cases were later confirmed in Lagos bringing the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 373. 99 have been discharged, with 11 deaths recorded. 